about.description:
Currently it supports basic functionality such as creating new notebooks,
opening any notebook in your filesystem and saving notebooks at any location.

name: spyder-notebook
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "spyder-notebook" %}
{% set version = "0.1.4" %}
{% set hash_type = "sha256" %}
{% set hash = "0cc18320452dfb38092bf04cda48ef53270a516e83af9667852d9a5f3ef0c60d" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  {{ hash_type }}: {{ hash }}

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record=record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools

  run:
    - python
    - spyder >=3.2
    - notebook >=4.3
    - qtpy
    - requests
    - psutil
    - nbformat

test:
  imports:
    # Linux is giving a segfault probably due to the lack of an X server
    # OS X fails to due some issue with Qt unrelated to this recipe
    - spyder_notebook  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/spyder-ide/spyder-notebook
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Jupyter notebook integration with Spyder'
  description: |
    Currently it supports basic functionality such as creating new notebooks, 
    opening any notebook in your filesystem and saving notebooks at any location.
  dev_url: https://github.com/spyder-ide/spyder-notebook

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - dalthviz
    - ccordoba12
    - goanpeca
    - jitseniesen
